1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,365
Welcome to the Attachment Pattern
Reflection.

2
00:00:04,365 --> 00:00:10,123
This practice helps you notice how
protective parts may respond to

3
00:00:10,123 --> 00:00:13,932
closeness, distance, repair, and
connection.

4
00:00:31,932 --> 00:00:31,932
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

5
00:00:31,932 --> 00:00:35,369
This is not about labeling yourself.

6
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:39,827
It is about understanding patterns with
compassion.

7
00:00:39,827 --> 00:00:42,474
Begin by settling your body.

8
00:00:42,474 --> 00:00:44,982
Take a slow breath in.

9
00:00:53,982 --> 00:00:53,982
<break time="3s" />

10
00:00:53,982 --> 00:00:56,118
And let it out.

11
00:00:56,118 --> 00:01:01,412
Bring to mind a recent relationship
moment that felt activating.

12
00:01:01,412 --> 00:01:03,873
Choose something manageable.

13
00:01:03,873 --> 00:01:07,170
Not the most overwhelming moment.

14
00:01:07,170 --> 00:01:09,213
Notice what happened.

15
00:01:09,213 --> 00:01:12,278
Did a part want closeness?

16
00:01:24,278 --> 00:01:24,278
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

17
00:01:24,278 --> 00:01:27,204
Did a part want distance?

18
00:01:39,204 --> 00:01:39,204
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

19
00:01:39,204 --> 00:01:42,315
Did a part seek reassurance?

20
00:01:54,315 --> 00:01:54,315
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

21
00:01:54,315 --> 00:01:56,916
Did a part shut down?

22
00:02:08,916 --> 00:02:08,916
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

23
00:02:08,916 --> 00:02:11,749
Did a part become guarded?

24
00:02:23,749 --> 00:02:23,749
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

25
00:02:23,749 --> 00:02:29,080
Did a part feel confused, wanting
connection and protection at the same

26
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:29,461
time?

27
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:41,461
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

28
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:46,244
Now ask: What did my system believe was
at stake in that moment?

29
00:02:58,244 --> 00:02:58,244
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

30
00:02:58,244 --> 00:03:06,289
Maybe being abandoned, overwhelmed,
rejected, controlled, unseen, too much,

31
00:03:06,289 --> 00:03:07,811
or not enough.

32
00:03:07,811 --> 00:03:11,573
Now notice the protective strategy.

33
00:03:11,573 --> 00:03:20,531
Did you reach, withdraw, please, protest,
freeze, explain, avoid, perform, become

34
00:03:20,531 --> 00:03:23,554
critical, or become silent?

35
00:03:35,554 --> 00:03:35,554
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

36
00:03:35,554 --> 00:03:40,477
Ask the protective part: What were you
trying to protect me from?

37
00:03:52,477 --> 00:03:52,477
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

38
00:03:52,477 --> 00:03:53,731
Listen.

39
00:04:11,731 --> 00:04:11,731
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

40
00:04:11,731 --> 00:04:16,932
Now ask: What did a younger or more
vulnerable part need in that moment?

41
00:04:28,932 --> 00:04:28,932
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

42
00:04:28,932 --> 00:04:36,182
Maybe reassurance, consistency, space,
repair, honesty, gentleness, or

43
00:04:36,182 --> 00:04:37,338
boundaries.

44
00:04:37,338 --> 00:04:43,097
Ask: What would Self-energy have offered
in that moment?

45
00:04:55,097 --> 00:04:55,097
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

46
00:04:55,097 --> 00:05:05,197
Maybe calm, clarity, a boundary, a repair
attempt, a pause, a request, or a kind

47
00:05:05,197 --> 00:05:05,964
truth.

48
00:05:05,964 --> 00:05:11,908
Now imagine replaying the moment with a
little more Self-energy present.

49
00:05:23,908 --> 00:05:23,908
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

50
00:05:23,908 --> 00:05:25,905
Not perfectly.

51
00:05:25,905 --> 00:05:28,784
Just one small change.

52
00:05:28,784 --> 00:05:30,456
What would you say?

53
00:05:42,456 --> 00:05:42,456
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

54
00:05:42,456 --> 00:05:44,221
What would you do?

55
00:05:56,221 --> 00:05:56,221
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

56
00:05:56,221 --> 00:05:58,497
What would you not do?

57
00:06:10,497 --> 00:06:10,497
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

58
00:06:10,497 --> 00:06:12,494
What would you ask for?

59
00:06:24,494 --> 00:06:24,494
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

60
00:06:24,494 --> 00:06:30,650
Now ask: What attachment pattern do I
want to understand more gently, rather

61
00:06:30,650 --> 00:06:31,553
than judge?

62
00:06:43,553 --> 00:06:43,553
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

63
00:06:43,553 --> 00:06:46,479
Take a slow breath in.

64
00:06:55,479 --> 00:06:55,479
<break time="3s" />

65
00:06:55,479 --> 00:06:57,615
And let it out.

66
00:06:57,615 --> 00:07:01,841
Thank the parts that protect you in
relationships.

67
00:07:01,841 --> 00:07:04,256
They learned for a reason.

68
00:07:04,256 --> 00:07:08,296
And they can learn new options slowly,
with support.

